<p>There are a number of binary codes similar to Gray codes, including:
</p>
<ul><li><span class="anchor" id="Datex"></span>Datex codes or Giannini codes (1954), as described by Carl P. Spaulding,<sup id="cite&#95;ref-Spaulding&#95;1954&#95;7-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Spaulding_1954-7"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>7<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-Spaulding&#95;1965&#95;89-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Spaulding_1965-89"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>87<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-Wheeler&#95;1969&#95;90-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Wheeler_1969-90"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>88<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-Dokter-Steinhauer&#95;1973&#95;91-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Dokter-Steinhauer_1973-91"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>89<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-Dokter-Steinhauer&#95;1975&#95;92-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Dokter-Steinhauer_1975-92"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>90<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-MIL&#95;1991&#95;6-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-MIL_1991-6"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>6<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> use a variant of <a href="#O&#39;Brien_II">O'Brien code&#160;II</a>.</li>
<li><span class="anchor" id="Varec"></span> Codes used by Varec (c. 1954),<sup id="cite&#95;ref-Varec&#95;1954&#95;93-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Varec_1954-93"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>91<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-Bishup-Repeta-Giarrizzo&#95;1963&#95;94-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Bishup-Repeta-Giarrizzo_1963-94"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>92<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-Whessoe&#95;1993&#95;95-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Whessoe_1993-95"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>93<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-Emerson&#95;96-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Emerson-96"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>94<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> use a variant of <a href="#O&#39;Brien_I">O'Brien code I</a> as well as base-12 and base-16 Gray code variants.</li>
<li><span class="anchor" id="Lucal"></span><span class="anchor" id="MRB"></span>Lucal code (1959)<sup id="cite&#95;ref-Lucal&#95;1959&#95;97-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Lucal_1959-97"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>95<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-Sellers-Hsiao-Bearnson&#95;1968&#95;98-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Sellers-Hsiao-Bearnson_1968-98"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>96<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-Doran&#95;2007&#95;56-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Doran_2007-56"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>55<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> aka modified reflected binary code (MRB)<sup id="cite&#95;ref-Lucal&#95;1959&#95;97-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Lucal_1959-97"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>95<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-Sellers-Hsiao-Bearnson&#95;1968&#95;98-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Sellers-Hsiao-Bearnson_1968-98"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>96<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-NB&#95;Modified&#95;99-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-NB_Modified-99"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>nb 3<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup></li>
