2<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-Foss&#95;1954&#95;2&#95;118-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Foss_1954_2-118"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>113<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> and used by <a href="#Varec">Varec</a> in 1954. Later, it was also known as Watts code or Watts reflected decimal (WRD) code and is sometimes ambiguously referred to as reflected binary modified Gray code.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-Evans&#95;1958&#95;119-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Evans_1958-119"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>114<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-Evans&#95;1960&#95;18-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Evans_1960-18"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>18<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-Evans&#95;1961&#95;19-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Evans_1961-19"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>19<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-Benjamin-Nicholls&#95;1963&#95;120-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Benjamin-Nicholls_1963-120"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>115<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-Klinkowski&#95;1964&#95;121-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Klinkowski_1964-121"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>116<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-Klinkowski&#95;1966&#95;122-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Klinkowski_1966-122"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>117<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-EDN&#95;1967&#95;123-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-EDN_1967-123"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>118<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-Toth-Zentai&#95;1979&#95;124-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Toth-Zentai_1979-124"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>119<spa